Background

		Mr. Hill Arnold Feinberg serves as Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of Hilltop Securities. Mr. Feinberg served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Hilltop Securities Inc. since 1991. Mr. Feinberg served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer at First Southwest Holdings, Inc. He has total of 25 years in this industry, majority of the time as Managing Director at Bear, Stearns & Co Inc., Dallas, TX. Prior positions included ... Senior Managing Director of Bear Stearns & Co. and Vice President and Manager of Salomon Brothers' Dallas office. He joined the United States Army Corps of Engineers, serving as 1st Lieutenant in Vietnam from 1970 to 1971. He serves as the Chairman of Phoenix House Foundation, Inc. He was chairman of the Municipal Securities Rulemaking Board. He served as  an Independent Non Executive Director at Energy XXI Ltd. (Former Name: Energy XXI (Bermuda) Limited) from May 7, 2007 to December 30, 2016 and served as  its Lead Independent Director from February 2, 2011 to December 30, 2016. He served as a Director for PlainsCapital Corporation since December 31, 2008. He serves as a Director of First Southwest Company. He has been a Director of Hilltop Holdings Inc. since November 30, 2012. He served as a Director of Texas Regional Bancshares Inc. since 2005. He served a Director of First Southwest Holdings, LLC. His civic and charitable service includes Board Member of the cardiopulmonary Research Science and Technology Institute, a Member of the Executive Committee of St. Mark's School of Texas and a Board Member of Visitors of UT Southwestern Health System. He was the Chairman of the Board of Directors of the MBM Foundation. Mr. Feinberg holds his Bachelor's degree in Finance from the University of Georgia in 1969, receiving the Distinguished Alumnus Award from the University of Georgia's Terry College of Business in May 2008.Read Full Background




